com.nabto.api

Class NabtoApi

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nabto.api.NabtoApi

  • public class NabtoApi
extends java.lang.Object
    Nabto client API.

    Example:

    
 NabtoApi api = new NabtoApi(new NabtoAndroidAssetManager(this));
 NabtoStatus status = api.startup();
 if (status == NabtoStatus.OK) {
     Session session = api.openSession("guest", "");
     if (session.getStatus() == NabtoStatus.OK) {
         String url = "nabto://demo1.nabduino.net/temperature.json?";
         UrlResult result = client.fetchUrl(url, session);
         if (result.getStatus() == NabtoStatus.OK) {
             String html = new String(result.getResult());
             // do something with HTML string
         }
         api.closeSession(session);
     }
     api.shutdown();
 }

      • startup

        public NabtoStatus startup()
        Initializes the Nabto client API.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: The path to home directory wasn't found OR error in the C API wrapper

      • shutdown

        public NabtoStatus shutdown()
        Terminates the Nabto client API.

        Releases any resources held by the Nabto client API. After each successful call to startup() call this function when the Nabto client API is no longer needed. This function can block for a small amount of time until all current sessions has closed properly.

        Upon return the Nabto client API is no longer available. The Nabto client API can be re-initialized by calling startup() again.

        Returns:
        NabtoStatus.OK is the only value returned.

      • probeNetwork

        public NabtoStatus probeNetwork(int timeoutMillis,
                                java.lang.String hostname)
        Try to connect to probe service to test for network connectivity.

        If NULL is specified as host, the portal host name from the configuration is used.

        The startup() function must have been called prior to calling this function.

        This function can be used to make the underlying platform start the network.

        Parameters:
        timeoutMillis - timeout before concluding a connection could not be established.
        hostname - hostname of probe service to connect to, using default if NULL.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.NO_NETWORK: The host couldn't be reached.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Error in the C API wrapper.

      • createProfile

        public NabtoStatus createProfile(java.lang.String email,
                                 java.lang.String password)
        Creates a Nabto client profile (private key + signed certificate) on this computer for specified registered Nabto user.

        The base station needed to be contacted for signing certificates is read from the configuration file (default is www.nabto.com).

        This function will fail with NabtoStatus.PORTAL_LOGIN_FAILURE if the specified user was registered on a different portal such as www.nabtotest.com. So the user must either register on the portal expected by the Nabto client API or change urlPortalDomain in the configuration file to point to the portal where the user is registered.

        The given password is used to access the portal for specified user. The password will also be used for encrypting the private key.

        The startup() function must have been called prior to calling this function.

        Parameters:
        email - Email address of user, as registered on portal.
        password - Password for accessing portal for specified user.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.UNLOCK_PK_FAILED: Bad password was specified.
        • NabtoStatus.CERT_SAVING_FAILURE: Could not save signed certificate.
        • NabtoStatus.PORTAL_LOGIN_FAILURE: Invalid email and/or password.
        • NabtoStatus.CERT_SIGNING_ERROR: Failed to sign certificate request.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Lookup failed for some unspecified reason.

      • createSelfSignedProfile

        public NabtoStatus createSelfSignedProfile(java.lang.String commonName,
                                           java.lang.String password)
        Creates a Nabto self signed profile.

        The startup() function must have been called prior to calling this function.

        This creates a self signed certificate. The identity of such certificate cannot be trusted but the fingerprint of the certificate can be trusted in the device. This does not rely on the signup(String, String) function. After the profile has been created it can be used in the open session function.

        Parameters:
        commonName - The common name part of the selfsigned certificate which is going to be made.
        password - The password which protects the private key.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.UNLOCK_PK_FAILED: Bad password was specified.
        • NabtoStatus.CERT_SAVING_FAILURE: Could not save signed certificate.
        • NabtoStatus.PORTAL_LOGIN_FAILURE: Invalid email and/or password.
        • NabtoStatus.CERT_SIGNING_ERROR: Failed to sign certificate request.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Lookup failed for some unspecified reason.

      • openSession

        public Session openSession(java.lang.String id,
                           java.lang.String password)
        Starts a new Nabto data retrieval session using the specified profile.

        The email address given must be an id of an existing certificate for a certain Nabto enabled device. If the device is unencrypted, specify the empty string for the password argument.

        This function returns a session object that must be used in subsequent client API invocations.

        When the session is no longer needed, close it by using the closeSession(Session) function.

        The startup() function must have been called prior to calling this function.

        Parameters:
        id - The id of an existing certificate. Either an email address or commonName.
        password - Password for encrypted private key file. Specify an empty string for an unencrypted key file.
        Returns:
        A Session object. If the function succeeds, the return value of Session.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of Session.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.OPEN_CERT_OR_PK_FAILED: No matching profile found for the given email address.
        • NabtoStatus.UNLOCK_PK_FAILED: A bad password was specified in the password argument.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: The login failed for some unspecified reason.

        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Error in the C API wrapper.

      • closeSession

        public NabtoStatus closeSession(Session session)
        Closes the specified Nabto session, preventing further data retrieval.

        The session object passed to this function must be returned by a call to either openSession(String, String) or openSessionBare().

        Upon return the session object is no longer valid.

        Parameters:
        session - session object
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session object was invalid.

      • rpcSetDefaultInterface

        public RpcResult rpcSetDefaultInterface(java.lang.String interfaceDefinition,
                                        Session session)
        Sets the default RPC interface to use when later invoking rpcInvoke(String, Session).

        Can be overriden for specific hosts with rpcSetInterface(String, String, Session).

        The session object given must have been obtained by a call to openSession(String, String) or openSessionBare().

        If a non-API level error occurred (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE), RpcResult.getJson() contains error details. Otherwise, the JSON string is undefined.

        Parameters:
        interfaceDefinition - The interface definition as XML formatted string.
        session - session handle.
        Returns:
        A RpcResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE: An error occurred with details in RpcResult.getJson().
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred handling the request.

      • rpcInvoke

        public RpcResult rpcInvoke(java.lang.String nabtoUrl,
                           Session session)
        Retrieves data synchronously from specified nabto://URL on specified session.

        As compared to fetchUrl(String, Session), this function only supports function invocation and not displaying contents of an HTML DD bundle. This also means the interface file is to specified prior to invocation using either rpcSetInterface(String, String, Session) or rpcSetDefaultInterface(String, Session)

        The session object given must have been obtained by a call to openSession(String, String) or openSessionBare().

        On successful return (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), RpcResult.getJson() contains a JSON response representing the response document. If a non-API level error occurred (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE), RpcResult.getJson() contains error details in JSON format.

        On successful return (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), RpcResult.getJson() returns a JSON response representing the response document. Otherwise, the JSON string is undefined.

        Parameters:
        nabtoUrl - The URL to retrieve.
        session - session handle.
        Returns:
        A RpcResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK and RpcResult.getJson() returns the JSON response. If the function fails, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE: An error occurred, details can be found in JSON format in the response.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred handling the request.

      • fetchUrl

        public UrlResult fetchUrl(java.lang.String nabtoUrl,
                          Session session)
        Retrieves data synchronously from specified nabto://URL on specified session.

        The session object given must have been obtained by a call to openSession(String, String) or openSessionBare().

        On successful return (UrlResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), UrlResult.getResult() returns the HTML code. The MIME type of the data is returned by UrlResult.getMimeType().

        Parameters:
        nabtoUrl - The URL to retrieve.
        session - session handle.
        Returns:
        A UrlResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK and UrlResult.getResult() returns the HTML code. If the function fails, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred handling the request.

      • submitPostData

        public UrlResult submitPostData(java.lang.String nabtoUrl,
                                byte[] postData,
                                java.lang.String postMimeType,
                                Session session)
        Submits specified data synchronously to specified URL through specified session.

        If destination host is HTTP enabled, use HTTP POST semantics for the submission. Note: Only "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" type data is currently supported as data for submission (any type of data may still be retrieved, though).

        The session object given must have been obtained by a call to openSession(String, String) or openSessionBare().

        On successful return (UrlResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), UrlResult.getResult() returns the HTML code. The MIME type of the data is returned by UrlResult.getMimeType().

        Parameters:
        nabtoUrl - The URL to submit data to.
        postData - The data to submit.
        postMimeType - MIME type of data to submit.
        session - session handle.
        Returns:
        A UrlResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred handling the request.

      • streamOpen

        public Stream streamOpen(java.lang.String nabtoHost,
                         Session session)
        Opens a stream on an existing session to a Nabto enabled device.

        This function returns a stream handle that must be used in subsequent client API invocations.

        The caller must call streamClose(Stream) when the stream is no longer needed.

        An open session handle must have been created prior to calling this function.

        Parameters:
        nabtoHost - The host to open a stream to.
        session - session handle
        Returns:
        A Stream object. If the function succeeds, the return value of Stream.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of Stream.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.STREAMING_UNSUPPORTED: Peer does not support streaming.
        • NabtoStatus.CONNECT_TO_HOST_FAILED: Could not connect to specified host.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred creating the stream.

      • streamClose

        public NabtoStatus streamClose(Stream stream)
        Closes an open stream.

        The return value is NabtoStatus.DATA_PENDING if unacknowledged data is still pending on the stream. Keep invoking streamClose(Stream) until the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. Alternatively close the owing session to force closing all the open streams with pending data.

        The handle passed to streamClose(Stream) must previously have been opened by a call to streamOpen(String, Session).

        Parameters:
        stream - stream handle
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_STREAM: Stream object was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.DATA_PENDING: Unacknowledged data is pending.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred closing the stream.

      • streamRead

        public StreamReadResult streamRead(Stream stream)
        Reads some data from an open stream.

        This call blocks based on the stream option set by streamSetOption(Stream, NabtoStreamOption, int):

        • NabtoStreamOption.RECEIVE_TIMEOUT = -1: blocking (default)
        • NabtoStreamOption.RECEIVE_TIMEOUT = 0: non-blocking
        • NabtoStreamOption.RECEIVE_TIMEOUT = n: blocks for up to n milliseconds.

        The stream handle given must have been obtained by a call to streamOpen(String, Session).

        On successful return (StreamReadResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), (StreamReadResult.getData()} returns the received data. Otherwise, the received data array is undefined.

        Parameters:
        stream - stream handle
        Returns:
        A StreamReadResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of StreamReadResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK and StreamReadResult.getData() returns the received data. If the function fails, the return value of Stream.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_STREAM: Stream handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.STREAM_CLOSED: The stream was closed gracefully.
        • NabtoStatus.ABORTED: The operation was aborted.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred reading the stream.

      • streamWrite

        public NabtoStatus streamWrite(Stream stream,
                               byte[] data)
        Writes given data to a stream.

        This call blocks based on the stream option set by streamSetOption(Stream, NabtoStreamOption, int):

        • NabtoStreamOption.SEND_TIMEOUT = -1: blocking until all data is sent or queued (default)
        • NabtoStreamOption.SEND_TIMEOUT = 0: non-blocking
        • NabtoStreamOption.SEND_TIMEOUT = n: blocks for up to n milliseconds.

        The stream handle given must have been obtained by a call to streamOpen(String, Session).

        If NabtoStatus.BUFFER_FULL is returned you must retransmit the data, no data has been queued. If NabtoStatus.OK is returned all the data is queued in the transmission queue.

        Parameters:
        stream - stream handle
        data - data to write
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_STREAM: Stream handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.BUFFER_FULL: There's not room for the bytes in the send queue.
        • NabtoStatus.STREAM_CLOSED: The stream was closed gracefully.
        • NabtoStatus.ABORTED: The operation was aborted.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred writing the stream.

      • streamConnectionType

        public NabtoConnectionType streamConnectionType(Stream stream)
        Retrieve the Nabto connection type of the underlying connection for the given stream.
        Parameters:
        stream - stream handle
        Returns:
        The connection type. If the function fails due to an unintialized Nabto client (see startup()), an invalid stream handle, or any unspecified error, NabtoConnectionType.UNKNOWN is returned.

      • tunnelOpenTcp

        public Tunnel tunnelOpenTcp(int localPort,
                            java.lang.String nabtoHost,
                            java.lang.String remoteHost,
                            int remotePort,
                            Session session)
        Opens a TCP tunnel to a remote server through a Nabto enabled device.

        In case the TCP tunnel should connect to the Nabto enabled device itself - that is the device is the server - specify "localhost" in the remoteHost parameter.

        This function returns a tunnel handle that must be used in subsequent client API invocations.

        The caller must call tunnelClose(Tunnel) when the tunnel is no longer needed.

        If zero is chosen for localPort, the client chooses a suitable port. After successful connection use tunnelInfo(Tunnel)} to get the listening port.

        An open session handle must have been created prior to calling this function.

        After successful return one is now able to connect to the local TCP port and communicate with the remote server. 

        
      +--------+           +--------+               +--------+
      | nabto  |   nabto   | nabto  |   tcp/ip      | remote |
   |--+ client +----~~~----+ device +----~~~-----|--+ server |
 port | API    |           | "host" |          port |        |
      +--------+           +--------+               +--------+
        Parameters:
        localPort - The local TCP port to listen on (0 = PORT_ANY)
        nabtoHost - The remote Nabto host to connect to.
        remoteHost - The host the remote endpoint establishes a TCP connection to.
        remotePort - The TCP port to connect to on remoteHost.
        session - The session handle returned by a previous call to the  openSession(String, String) or openSessionBare() function.
        Returns:
        A Tunnel object. If the function succeeds, the return value of Tunnel.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of Tunnel.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred creating the tunnel.

      • tunnelClose

        public NabtoStatus tunnelClose(Tunnel tunnel)
        Closes an open tunnel.

        The tunnel handle given must have been obtained by a call to tunnelOpenTcp(int, String, String, int, Session).

        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_STREAM_OPTION: Option is invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred closing the tunnel.

      • tunnelInfo

        public TunnelInfoResult tunnelInfo(Tunnel tunnel)
        Retrieves information on an (open) tunnel.

        The tunnel handle given must have been obtained by a call to tunnelOpenTcp(int, String, String, int, Session).

        On succesful return (TunnelInfoResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), TunnelInfoResult.getTunnelState() returns the tunnel state and TunnelInfoResult.getPort()} returns the listening port. If the function fails both output parameters are undefined.

        Parameters:
        tunnel - tunnel handle
        Returns:
        A TunnelInfoResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of Tunnel.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK and it contains valid result parameters. If the function fails, the return value of TunnelInfoResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED: The startup() function is the first function to call to initialize the Nabto client.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_TUNNEL: Tunnel handle was invalid.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: An unspecified error occurred retrieving the tunnel info.
